	3.1 IRC  <URL:#tn=	3.1 IRC >
		3.1.1 A Guide to getting onto IRC  <URL:#tn=		3.1.1 A Guide to getting onto IRC >
1. Go in IRC. Get the nick you want using /nick {NICK} <URL:#tn=1. Go in IRC. Get the nick you want using /nick {NICK}>
2. In the status box, type /msg nickserv register {PASSWORD} {EMAIL} <URL:#tn=2. In the status box, type /msg nickserv register {PASSWORD} {EMAIL}>
3. Confirm your email address by following the instructions it contains. <URL:#tn=3. Confirm your email address by following the instructions it contains.>
4. When you log in, you will need to identify. If you have a section in your client to automatically perform commands on startup, put this there, otherwise, just type it in. /msg nickserv identify {PASSWORD} <URL:#tn=4. When you log in, you will need to identify. If you have a section in your client to automatically perform commands on startup, put this there, otherwise, just type it in. /msg nickserv identify {PASSWORD}>
5. Once done, if you want to prevent others using your nick use /msg nickserv set enforce on <URL:#tn=5. Once done, if you want to prevent others using your nick use /msg nickserv set enforce on>
6. If someone (or you) tries to use your nick and fails to identify, it will lock it. use /msg nickserv release {NICK} {PASSWORD} to unlock it. <URL:#tn=6. If someone (or you) tries to use your nick and fails to identify, it will lock it. use /msg nickserv release {NICK} {PASSWORD} to unlock it.>
7. If at any time you forget a command. Use /msg nickserv help <URL:#tn=7. If at any time you forget a command. Use /msg nickserv help>
