			1.2.1.7 Claws

				1.2.1.7.1 [291 R] shadowphnx's Gravebone and Trolls Deck
I am very excited to share with all of you my really fun to play 336 rated (9/25/16) Graveboneicon deck. 

| Why should you play this deck? 
| 1. If you like reviving Eternal Trolls and Phoenix Urigons to the dismay of your opponent
| 2. If you like to play Supernovaicon where only your opponent's allies get wiped
| 3. And if you are very cold, you like to use the Voice of Wintericon so that only your opponent's allies stay frozen

then this is the deck for you!

Hero: Graveboneicon
Allies: (19)
4x Feasterling
2x Ironhide Karashicon
4x Eternal Troll
3x Infernal Gargoyleicon
4x Phoenix Urigonicon
2x Dakrathicon

Abilities: (19)
4x Sacrificial Lambicon
4x Bad Santaicon
3x Relentless Savagery
4x Fireballicon
4x Supernovaicon

Weapons: (3)
3x Voice of Wintericon

Deck Explanation:
There are a number of ways to secure victory in the deck, but the main goal is board control.
Here are some combos to look out for:

Feasterling + Relentless Savagery = 5 attack, enough to kill many 3 and 4 turn allies.

Eternal Troll + Eternal Troll + Relentless Savagery = As you crash your Eternal Troll into your opponent's allies, Relentless Savagery will return to your hand when the Troll dies and you can play it again. I have killed opposing Dakraths this way.

Supernova + Eternal Troll or Phoenix Urigonicon = Wipe the board with your allies still in play!

Voice of Winter + Sacrificial Lambicon + Eternal Troll or Phoenix Urigon = Get rid of the frozen status of your allies while drawing 3 cards. (As Buqs pointed out, for the Eternal Troll, you should wait until the turn after you summoned it to use Sacrificial Lamb so that it doesn't die.).

Voice of Winter + Supernova + Eternal Troll or Phoenix Urigon = An alternative method for getting rid of the frozen status of your allies.

Voice of Winter + Dakrathicon = Dakrath can't be frozen and is very hard to kill. Also a worthy candidate for revival.

Gravebone + Voice of Winter = Allies that Gravebone returns to play won't be frozen by Voice of Winter!

Sacrificial Lamb + Gravebone = Kill your possibly incapacitated ally and then revive it!

General Tips

Voice of Winter is a weapon, you can and often should attack with it. Don't forget this! Especially if your opponent is playing item destruction.
This can easily amount to 2 or 3 damage to the opponent as there is a good chance your opponent will not have
the item destruction in their hand when you play it. However also be careful that you don't cause your Voice of Winter to die either.

Bad Santaicon is a really great card if you anticipate your opponent having a really strong draw engine. Otherwise be careful about playing it.

If you have any thoughts, suggestions or comments, let me know

-Shadowphnx
