				1.6.1.1.3
			1.6.1.2 Kylt's Zhanna 2: Banish Control
			http://www.shadowera.com/showthread.php?26966-Kylt-s-Zhanna-2-Banish-Control&p=427756#post427756
Hi. Here is my another Zhanna deck. 

Previous Zhanna that I posted here was aggro heavy. You can go get the board with ice storm, while having Priest's almighty tools to control the game. This deck is control heavy, meaning that you let your opponent be the beatdown and you stay passive until you get to finish the game.

This deck might be difficult to play for new players as you need to know what your opponent is doing. But once you know about many heroes and decks, you can play this deck without thinking too much because this deck has a golden strategy just like rush Eladwenicon. 

I play this deck when I feel like I just wanna play SE without using my head but not quite in the mood for rush Elad 

(My aggro Zhanna deck is here: http://www.shadowera.com/showthread....p-winning-deck )




DECK

***HERO***
Zhanna Misticon

***Allies (17)***
4x Jasmine Roseculticon
2x Aeon Stormcallericon
3x Layarian Seductress
4x Elizabeth Winterborn
4x Knight of the Golden Dawn

***Abilities (19)***
4x Tidal Waveicon
4x Focused Prayericon
4x Retreaticon!
1x Forgiveness
4x Banish
2x Mass Purification

***Armors (2)***
2x The King's Prideicon

***Weapons (4)***
4x Wizent's Stafficon

TOTAL: 42 cards + Hero


This deck is all about gaining advantage.


You have 4 retreat, 4 banish, 4 TW = 12 ability cards to control the board, while you also have 4 Jasmine and 3 Seductress for extra ally control. Too much? Maybe. But this makes your sac choice so much easier. 

Shutting down your opponent's draw is the first thing you need to do. And then get you draw engine on the board. From there, you can counter every card opponent plays, thereby leaving them nothing to fight with. Use Banish for 1:1 trade, TW is for 2 for 1 trade, while you are drawing 2 or 3 cards every turn. Accumulate hand advantage first, then turn that into board advantage when your opponent has not many ways to counter.

Type: Control
Resource: 7~9
Speed: Slow and Passive until you win the game.




Cards

3cc allies here can be swapped/mixed to what you like. 

Jasmine
Solid 3/4 and strong ability. Never less than 3 in any DP priest deck imo.

Seductress
Since KotGD have 4 atk, Aldonicon is less important here. Seductress alone can buy a lot of time for you to cast control card while presenting a body on the board, forcing your opponent to deal with it. Also, nice alt way to deal with steadfast allies other than Tidal Wave.

Other possibilities are,

Aldon
As I wrote above, since this deck's main finisher has 4 atk, and also 1 ping damage from Wizent's Staff is usually enough, Aldon's +1 boost is less important. But still, being able to buff KotGD to kill IG/MA/PB in 1 hit is nothing to ignore. 

FFM
Actually pretty cool in this deck because in any control deck, more ways to make your hand better is never a bad thing. Especially, with this deck, you need to have correct answers for opponent's play throughout the game. FFM greatly helps you to reach the card you need in the situation. Also, KP+FFM ftw. 


KotGD
Pretty powerful. Game finisher No 1. I don't say it is absolutely better than Ravenicon or Brax soldier, but KotGD allows you to use Aldon's slot for something else. He is better than Raven to face Jasmine, Aldon or DMT. Plus, he has to be killed in 1 turn or Zhanna can gain 6 point advantage. So he actually has a good survivability when Zhanna has SE stock. Overall, KotGD fits well in Zhanna control deck.


Elizabeth
4 copies because you need a massive draw power. You can swap 1 Elizabeth with TO if you like, but never bring less than 3 copies. 

Aeon
Finisher No 2. He requires your opponent to have pretty specific cards to counter: Dragon's tooth/MC etc. Note that getting a retreat on Aeon is good for you because opponent have used 1 card and did not gain much tempo since Zhanna have multiple ways to counter allies on the board that came along with the retreat. You must kill opponent draw engine first, then getting an Aeon retreated hurts your opponent more. +1 Aeon, -1 KotGD works too.


Tidal Wave
Big advantage gaining card. Auto 4 in this type of deck.

Banish
Quite expensive, but it gives your opponent no hand advantage, unlike retreat. Since it costs 4 resource to cast, your aim is to get to 7 or 8 resource for Banish + something (Or even double Banish!)

Retreat
Cheap and good. Not as great as Banish, in terms of diminishing opponent's hand advantage, but Zhanna needs 2cc ability cards to cast on t2 to delay opponent's rush. 

FP
Best item destruction card in the game. It is a bit easier to use FP on Tome or DoU against portal majiya than normal Zhanna build, because Banish can take care of SK portal combo to a degree. Auto 4 in passive control deck.

Mass Purification
Another advantage gaining card. MP is like TW against certain decks. +1 MP and -1 retreat/banish for attachment heavy meta. 

Forgiveness
AUTO 1 include!


Wizent staff
Draw more without using your precious resource! W.Staff = BF if you like.

KP
Finisher No 3.


Plays

t4 Staff, t5 TW, t6 retreat+Elizabeth, t7 Banish + Jas.
t4 draw engine, t5 retreat + FP, t6 TW, t7 retreat + KotG, t8 double Banish etc.


Have fun!


Any questions?



P.S.
You can do almost the same with Jerichoicon. He cannot use Elizabeth and KotGD well, but he can exclude MP so the deck will be more lean and probability of drawing key cards goes up. 

			1.6.1.3 Kylt's Zhanna: popup winning deck
Since I don't belong to any guild, I have no obligation to keep the deck list secret.
I hope this helps for new players who want to start playing DP Priest. This deck brought me to 340 rating.

Cost of making this deck (29th April 2013)
13,550 Gold


***HERO***
Zhanna Misticon

***Allies (19)***
4x Jasmine Roseculticon
2x Aldon the Braveicon
2x Armored Sandwormicon
2x Aeon Stormcallericon
1x Braxnorian Soldier
3x Champion of Irum
2x Layarian Seductress
3x Elizabeth Winterborn

***Abilities (15)***
3x Tidal Waveicon
3x Ice Stormicon
3x Focused Prayericon
4x Retreaticon!
1x Forgiveness
1x Mass Purification

***Armors (2)***
2x The King's Prideicon

***Weapons (4)***
4x Wizent's Stafficon

TOTAL: 40 cards + Hero


This deck is quite difficult to play.
You need to know when to go for the board and when to give up and Tidal Wave.
However, the deck is capable of winning without using a single TW if played correctly.
So many synergies in this deck, so fun to play. Knowing what your opponent's optimal play in what turn is crucial.

Type: Control
Resource: 6~7
Speed: Can be fast but usually slow.



Champion of Irum
Great with Zhanna's ability. Always drop this on T2 when you have it in hand.
CoI - Aldon can punish opponent Karash when going second. 
CoI - L Seductress is great against human when going second.
CoI - Ice Storm can take out enemy Karash and DMT. A clear board is there.
Also, you can play CoI with TW at 7 resource.
Attack with him, and heal him with Zhanna's ability on t3.
He is unique so I only included 3. But really, if you get him on t2, your probability to win rises by quite a lot.

Jasmine
Best t3 play when going first.
If you managed to keep her behind Aeon, you won the game there.
No better 3cc ally than her, so 4. 

Aldon
He became more important in DP, mainly because of Karash.
Himself is not great against Karash but he is the second optimal t3 drop when going first.

L Seductress
the only way to deal with allies with Steadfast from your hand except TW.
I don't know how many times she saved me in games. Keep her in hand if you have enough allies on board, otherwise, play her. It is always better to have allies on your board in this deck.

Elizabeth
People still don't know how to deal with her. She is sooo dangerous.
While health 5 is not easy to kill in one turn, Zhanna can heal her up for more draws.
t4 Liz when going first is very strong. 

Sandworm
For me, Sandworm is better than Ravenicon as I want to play 5cc on its own.
Raven, or KotGD sometimes need to be backed up with a retreat - Sandworm does not need it.
It can do nothing against Karash though. That's why I decided to include Ice Storm.

Brax Soldier
Just there to take care of Portalicon Majiyaicon. Better than Sandworm against Lanceicon. 
3 Sandworm instead of 2 and 1 Brax Soldier is more consistent and that's what I usually use in QMs.

Aeon
Drop him after your opponent uses ability cards on Elizabeth/Sandworms.
Elizabeth - Sandworm - Aeon - KP is how I win 30% of times.



Tidal Wave
Arguably Priest's most powerful card.
However, it is always better not to rely on TW, because playing TW means giving up a turn and opponent can start playing more threats.
I believe in my deck and my draw so I usually sac TW. But for those who are not sure how my deck works should hold this in hand until you know when to sac TW.

Ice Storm
My biggest 'discovery' in DP. This card won me so many games. Totally underrated in every scene of the game. Trust me, this card is so good. Priests have had difficult times dealing with stealth allies. This is the answer. 
Sandworm + ice storm is a great surprise as your opponent do not expect to see a board wipe.
Great against Karash, W.savage, as well as stealth allies. Coincidentally, they ALL have only 2 health (except Erikaicon with 3 but no ambush so W.staff will deal the extra)!!! Or from a different perspective, this is a mini KP for 3 cost!

Focused Player
As I said, I believe in my deck and draw. So I only included 3.
This is a very powerful card and it has always been the one of reasons why I choose Zhanna to play in competitive scenes.
Since it is so powerful, you might want 4.

Retreat
One of MUST-INCLUDE card in any priest decks really.
Cheaper than new card Banish, and it does almost the same thing (for this deck anyway)
Knowing how to use retreat is not only crucial for this deck but for Shadow Era.

Forgiveness
One of the best card Priest got in DP. 
The idea to include 1 forgiveness came from my friend, BP Hachi. So the full credit goes to him. Thanks!
His idea to include this card have made my deck possible - I rarely have 4 of the same cards in the deck because I can always get it back with this. This is 4th (3rd for KP and Aeon) copy of any cards in the deck. Doesn't it sound amazing?

Note: On the Test Server, opponent's resource destruction messed the resource pile and I could not get the card I was supposed to get. I am not sure if this is the case in the live server but please be careful.

Mass purification
I rarely use it. But attachment destruction is good to have at least one in any deck anyway. Nevertheless, it has won me games several times against Wulven/Warrior heros. Also, this is the only way to remove Into the Foresticon.



The King's Pride (KP)
Very expensive for new players But you need this (2 is fine )
I know mage/zalader/banebow hate this card.

Wizent's staff
Main draw engine. Also this is a weapon which enables Zhanna to attack. Get full use out of it. Especially since Zhanna can heal up the damage. Use this as an additional 1 damage.
e.g. Jas + W.staff to take out 4 health ally. Zhanna attack to reduce the durability of Anklebreakericon/Dagger of Unmakingicon
But don't use too much SE when facing against a rush deck.



Have fun! But don't give up because you only played it for 5 times and didn't go well 
You need a lot of practice with this deck. Trust my build and play with it for 100 times 

Any questions?


Addition:
Some scenes I encountered on QM I think worths noting.

Kairos - TW or Seduce.
Serenaicon or Baduruuicon (with Night Prowlericon) - they discard (steal) a card from your hand at t5
Moonstalkericon - When this deck starts to shine, MS starts to hide.
Rush Elad - Without Healing Touchicon, you need to take care of their ally rush. Tools are CoI, Seductress, Ice Storm and W. Staff.
Majiya Portal S.Colossus - Don't expect KP to stay long.

			1.6.1.4 My World Champion winning Zhanna deck
Hello everyone!

Since I promised to post the deck, I have to deliver, so here it is.

First, and most important, the list:

1x Zhannaicon - 42 cards (Hero included)

Allies - 18
4x Jasmine Roseculticon
3x Aldon the Braveicon
4x Tainted Oracleicon
4x Raven Wildhearticon
3x Aeon Stormcallericon

Abilities - 17
4x Healing Touchicon
4x Tidal Waveicon
4x Focused Prayericon
1x Resurrectionicon 

4x Retreaticon

Weapons/Armors - 6
4x Wizent's Stafficon
2x King's Prideicon

Question: Why did I choose this deck for the WC?
Well, I've said it in the interview that's online, but obviously not everyone heard that. The reason I chose this deck is because it has no unwinnable matchups. Of course it has difficult matchups (I'll explain below) but in every matchup it's possible to go to at least 40-50% winrate. Of course, some matchups will require some experience, some proper thinking and the right saccing. I think most other decks really have a deck, you REALLY DON'T WANT TO FACE. Think as Zaladaricon a Gwen deck, Gwen with Moonstalkericon, Moonstalker with mages, mages with Ambericon, and so forth. With Zhanna that isn't really there, and that's why I made that pick.

Question: Is this an easy deck to play?
No. Not at all. Be prepared to lose a lot of games with it, if you want to try this deck out. It has a lot of different matchups that require a completely different approach, and you won't know all of these from the start.

Question: Can you explain the deck a bit?
Sure! I'll explain it on a card by card basis.

Jasmine Rosecult
Really, I have no idea how many games she has won me already, but it's uncountable. Her ability alone can win games. Protect her behind an Aeon and you're golden. Once she hits the board, your opponent HAS to deal with her, or he loses the game.

Aldon the Brave
Well, he's more there to add that extra bit of damage when you need it, and to have a body on turn 3 than anything else. Still, a good ally that can do a lot, still, it's best to play him after you already have something on the field, except if you want to draw fire away from your hero, and you have nothing else to play.

Tainted Oracle
A great card! Allows draw, makes it so your hero gets hit less, can be killed by your own deck if he gets disabled. All around great ally to have, and great draw 'engine'. By having 4 of those, and 4 times Wizent's Staff it's almost guaranteed to have some form of draw on turn 4. 

Raven
A completely underrated ally in the current meta. Having Raven is great vs Moonstalker (yes, you read that right). A lot of players use Sandwormicon nowadays, just because of the fact that it's a good ally. It's great versus Anklebreakericon, immune to dots, great versus Dagger of Unmakingicon and so on. Well yes, that's completely true, but it's a defensive ally. Playing it on an empty board doesn't guarantee board control, while playing a Raven does. Also does more damage. Can kill 5 health allies with KP and can still survive a nova.

Aeon
Mister bad-ass. Great cards versus decks that can't just instantly kill allies. Think about Banebowicon, warriors, even Lanceicon and Serenaicon sometimes. Drop him on the board as soon as you can. Even vs Elemental decks. Having your Aeon Mind Controlled doesn't hurt more than having your Jasmine Mind Controlled. So it almost never hurts to have him on the board. 

Healing Touch
Completely underrated and one of my favorite cards. It's just great in a LOT of matchups. Vs warriors it removes Crippling Blowicon, versus wulven it removes Captured Prey, versus mages it helps to stay alive a lot longer, same goes for Zaladar who tends to try to deathrace a lot. Negates Eladwenicon's ability. Removes distraction.
Ever played vs a Lance who hasted Ravens? Well that's what this card basically does. "Here, Crippling Blow, now your raven is completely useless! - Healing Touch, and Raven is immediately ready to attack."

Tidal Wave
The obvious card. Though, not as easy to use as people think. The trick is to get as most value out of the card as possible. For example, if you see your opponent has 2 allies on the board, and you have none, but he only has 4-5 damage output on the board, drop an Aeon instead and try to draw more fire to him, while at the same time try to keep your draw going. If he goes for the Aeon, good for you since it allows you to be aggressive, if he doesn't that means he committed more for the board, so now you'll get more out of your Tidal Wave. 

Focused Prayer
Use this card especially to take out draw engines. Vs mages though you might want to keep one in hand at all times, because it can save your life if you get to destroy a Portalicon with it, or a Dagger of Unmaking, which by the way can ruin your day. 

Resurrection 
Well, the card isn't used a lot, so the deck is probably better without this card. Though, I added the card to my deck because of mirror matchups and Millstalker. Since I never encountered these, I never got to play this card, so it's probably best to cut this card from the deck.

Retreat
Well yes, the obvious board control card. It's especially good on later turns. Play Tidal Wave on turn 6/7, and next turn you combine a retreat with a Raven or an Aeon. That wins you games right there.

Wizent's Staff
The basic draw engine. When fighting versus death racing decks, try not to rely on it too much, since it slows down your healing and thus you won't last as long. Which is the end what you aim for, lasting long.

King's Pride
Only use this card in desperate moments OR when the attack boost allows you to take down an ally you otherwise wouldn't have been able to take out in one blow. When you have an active ally on the board, and you can play a Kings Pride, it's often good game.

Question: Can you explain how you sac your cards with this deck?
I can. But I won't. Trial and error is the way to learn. If you want to learn how this deck works, I expect people to have the time to learn and understand the deck. 

Question: What are the weaknesses of this deck?
As I said, there isn't one HERO that is a weak spot, there are however deck ARCHETYPES that can be problematic. The most common and the most seen problematic deck is rush. Eladwen rush, Amber rush, Zaladar rush can all be quite problematic. The key is on trying to let your allies take some hits instead of your hero, keeping your draw up with Tainted Oracle and only Wizent's Staff if you have no other choice. Try to survive till the opponent runs out of steam (which he will if you focus down his draw engine, or high damage weapons), and then take the board with big fat allies. 

Another problematic things is Dagger of Unmaking. The best ways of destroying it is by spamming your 3cc allies and using Wizent's Staff to run the durability out, or obviously just to destroy it by using Focused Prayers. Be advised though, that destroying it with Focused Prayers may mean that you won't have one for destroying possible portals or Tome of Knowledges, so keep that in mind.

Last problematic thing is Shadow Knighticon. If you can't break the loop, you'll lose, that's for sure. So you have to try and break that loop. Your best ways in doing so is by playing either Jasmine or Raven. Both work equally well, so keep that in mind.

For the rest, I hope you enjoyed my explanation, and if you have any questions, I'll try and answer them in the thread. But please refrain from saying that you played the deck for 5 games and lost all of them, because you'll need at THE VERY LEAST 20 games to get the hang of the deck. 

P.S.: If you see any typing errors or other things that aren't correct, just say so and I'll update the OP

